A real sweetheart. Very knowledgable, organized, caring, and passionate. She is honestly one of the best professors I had during my undergrad. In order to get a high mark in her class, make sure you go over the lecture slides, and read the concepts in those slides from the textbook before class and an A would be very attainable.

Very intimidating, but overall, very knowledgeable. I'm in Finance but don't like the investments side, I think its all based on luck. However, I enjoyed learning the technical side of things. She doesn't just summarize the textbook, she gives you in depth analysis and shows you multiple approaches by applying the material in real life investments.
